{"word":"Pashur","slug":"pashur","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Pashur</b> <a href=\"#/H6583\">H6583</a> <br/> 1. A priest, son of Malchiah:<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=9&verse=12'>1Ch 9:12</a> <br/> - An influential man, and ancestor of an influential family<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=21&verse=1'>Jer 21:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=38&verse=1'>Jer 38:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=2&verse=38'>Ezr 2:38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=10&verse=22'>Ezr 10:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=7&verse=41'>Neh 7:41</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=10&verse=3'>Neh 10:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=11&verse=12'>Neh 11:12</a> <br/> 2. Son of Immer and governor of the temple. Beats and imprisons Jeremiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=20&verse=6'>Jer 20:6</a><br/> 3. Father of Gedaliah, who persecuted Jeremiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=38&verse=1'>Jer 38:1</a>"}]}